<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
</head>

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<style>
    body {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
        background: url('https://img.freepik.com/premium-photo/white-wall-with-white-background-that-says-white_689904-103927.jpg') no-repeat center center fixed;
        background-size: cover;
        margin: 0;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        color: #000000;
        justify-content: center;
        align-content: center;
    }

    .heading {
        font-weight: 900;
        font-size: 50px;
        color: rgb(16, 137, 211);
    }

    .heading2 {
        font-weight: 550;
        font-size: 30px;
        color: rgb(16, 137, 211);
    }

    .heading3 {
        font-weight: 80;
        font-size: 20px;
        color: rgb(16, 137, 211);
    }
</style>

<body>
    <div class="container" style="margin-bottom: 2cm; align-content:center;" ;>
        <h1 class="heading">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <br />
        <h3 class="heading2">User-Provided Information</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            When you use our forum, you may provide us with information such as your username, email address, and any additional information you choose to include in your posts.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            We may also collect certain information automatically when you visit the Site, including your IP address, browser type, and operating system. This information helps us improve the functionality and security of the Site.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">How We Use Your Information</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li class="heading3">To provide and maintain the forum functionality.</li>
            <li class="heading3">To personalize your experience on the forum.</li>
            <li class="heading3">To analyze and improve the Site's performance and user experience.</li>
            <li class="heading3">To communicate with you about updates, announcements, and other information related to the forum.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="heading2">Information Sharing</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personally identifiable information to outside parties. However, information you choose to share in forum posts will be visible to other users.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">Security</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">Your Choices</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            You can update or delete your forum posts and account information at any time. If you have questions or concerns about your privacy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@eStavba.com">support@eStavba.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">Changes to this Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The updated Privacy Policy will be effective when posted on the Site.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading2">Contact Us</h3>
        <p class="heading3">
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@eStavba.com">support@eStavba.com</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
